Z||000000||Riveler||06-19-2001||10:46 PM||riveler@uol.com.br||Boto is a name used to define river dolphins!<p>" In a full moon's night, in a fishermen or river villages, sometimes during certain celebrations, specially weddings, a gorgeous and strange man appears from nowhere, dressed elegantly in white using a hat also white. This strange man has a different way to walk: he swings his body at every step he makes. With this weird walk, all the girls and young women of the villages he visits strangely fall in love with him, but he denies all of them, gently yet strongly. All the villages's men ended up being jealous about him and throw out some unkind comments:<br>- Am I smelling rotten fish around here or someone else has forgotten to take a good bath?<br>- A fisherman he is not! None of us could buy those clothes! I bet he is a thief of something worse!<br>- What about that hat? Why doesn't he never take it off? Is he bald or have a bad haircut??<p>Despite all of these mocking and agressive words, he just bend his head and smile politely without saying anything. As the time passes by, he finally finds a beautiful and special girl and try to court her. When the girl agrees his court, they go away from the people and walk by the river's margins. There, at the margins he throw the girl in the river and jumps too, changing to his real form: a boto. Then, he takes the girl away to live in his realm, under the river's waters forever. When the girl denies him, he throw her at the river too, but this time he lets her die by drowning."<p>Wonderful story, huh? He never takes off his hat because of his nostrils on the top of his head and he really smells like a fish!<p>I think in USA, UK and Australia there's must be a different legend with dolphins. I would love to hear/read it!<p>Oh, I forgot to mention: he is a thief!
